The in-scope features define the functionalities that are included in the Smart Queue Management System for Banks. These features are essential for efficient queue handling and service management within bank branches.
In-Scope Features
1.	Customer Token Generation: Customers can generate virtual tokens for bank services through the system.
2.	Real-Time Queue Monitoring: Customers and staff can view the current queue status and token position in real time.
3.	Service Counter Management: The system allows assignment and management of multiple service counters.
4.	Calling Next Customer: Bank tellers can call the next token electronically from the system.
5.	Notification System: Customers receive alerts when their turn is approaching.
6.	User Authentication: Secure login for bank staff and administrators.
7.	Admin Dashboard: Bank administrators can monitor queue flow, counters, and performance statistics.
8.	Basic Reports: Generation of simple reports such as number of customers served and waiting time.
